BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
CATEGORIES:Cultural
DESCRIPTION:The purpose of this event is to bring awareness to those who a
 re and who have struggled with self harm/injury. March is the dedicated m
 onth of awareness for this. Through a tabling event\, we will provide a r
 esource card that explains what self harm\, triggers\, and urges are. On 
 the back there will be a “how to make a self care box” as it connects wit
 h other things to gravitate towards instead of self harm. There will alwa
 ys be organizations on the back\, connecting with self harm and ways to b
 e involved with bringing awareness. For the main activity\, students will
  make their own orange ribbon to wear or add to their bag in support of s
 elf-harm/injury month. While they make them\, we will discuss how student
 s are impacted by self-harm and additional ways they can support their pe
 ers. Another aspect of self-harm/injury awareness month is the butterfly 
 project\, which signifies a purpose behind why someone wants to stop self
 -harm/injury. With an invisible pen\, they can draw a butterfly when they
  have an urge. It gives purpose to what they’re doing by caring for a but
 terfly\, further supporting caring for themselves. They’re the only ones 
 who can see the butterfly once a light is shone upon it\, so it eliminate
 s possible judgement they might get from others as well.\nSkegg\, K. (200
 5\, October 22). Self-harm - the lancet. The Lancet. https://www.thelance
 t.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(05)67600-3/fulltext\nHetrick\
 , S. E.\, Subasinghe\, A.\, Anglin\, K.\, Hart\, L.\, Morgan\, A.\, & Rob
 inson\, J. (2020\, January 9). Understanding the needs of young people wh
 o engage in self-harm: A qualitative investigation. Frontiers. https://ww
 w.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2019.02916/f
 ull#S4\nFenton\, C.\, & Kingsley\, E. (2022\, September 14). Scoping revi
 ew: Alternatives to self‐harm recommended on Mental Health self‐help webs
 ites - fenton - 2023 - international journal of mental health nursing - w
 iley online library. Wiley Online Library. https://onlinelibrary.wiley.co
 m/doi/full/10.1111/inm.13067\nVunderl\, Š.\, & Krajnčan\, M. (2022). The 
 approaches in working with self-harmed students. Oblikovanje Inovativnih 
 Učnih Okolij\, 479–488. https://doi.org/10.26493/978-961-293-139-1.479-48
 8\n\nHosted by: U Bring Change to Mind\n\nAdditional Information can be f
 ound at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12371817
DTEND:20260331T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260331T050034Z
DTSTART:20260331T150000Z
LOCATION:Outside Ballantine Hall - Table 2
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Beauty In Butterflies
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12371817
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12371817
X-HOSTS:U Bring Change to Mind
