DESCRIPTION:Recovery Ally Training is an interactive educational workshop 
 designed to increase awareness\, reduce stigma\, and build practical skil
 ls to support individuals in recovery from substance use disorders. Parti
 cipants will learn about recovery pathways\, common challenges faced by p
 eople in recovery\, and how language\, policies\, and everyday interactio
 ns can either support or hinder recovery efforts.\nThis training emphasiz
 es empathy\, inclusivity\, and actionable strategies\, empowering partici
 pants to serve as visible\, informed allies within their communities\, wo
 rkplaces\, or campuses. By the end of the training\, attendees will have 
 a stronger understanding of recovery-oriented practices and how to create
  safer\, more supportive environments for people in recovery.\n\nHosted b
 y: Collegiate Recovery Community\n\nAdditional Information can be found a
 t: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12164957
DTEND:20260414T193000Z
