DESCRIPTION:This is our last book discussion meeting. What does it mean to
  be an "other"? How can writing shift the boundaries between insider and 
 outsider for both author and audience? All are welcome to join the ACC in
  discussing these questions over pizza. We will discuss the last two essa
 ys of Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay collection To Save and to Destroy: Writin
 g as an Other. Digital copies of the eBook are freely available to access
  through IU Libraries \n \nFor more information\, please reach out to ACC
  volunteer and book club moderator Cheryl Nong\, PhD student in social ps
 ychology\, at acc@iu.edu.    \n \nAll Indiana University events\, groups\
 , activities\, and educational\, cultural\, and historical observances we
 lcome all IU students and other members of the Indiana University communi
 ty.\n\nHosted by: Asian Culture Center\n\nAdditional Information can be f
 ound at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11950465
DTEND:20260414T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260331T050034Z
DTSTART:20260414T210000Z
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ACC Book Club features “To Save and Destroy” by Viet Nguyen
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11950465
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11950465
X-HOSTS:Asian Culture Center
END:VEVENT
