DESCRIPTION:3:30 - 4:00 p.m. | Curator-led Tour | Featured Exhibitions Gal
 lery   \nJoin us for a rare opportunity to explore the exhibition with Ta
 sha Kimmet\, Curator of Asian Art.  This is a guided tour that starts at 
 3:30 p.m. If you miss the tour\, you’re welcome to drop in to explore the
  exhibition at your own pace until 5 p.m.    \n4 - 5 p.m. | Reception | M
 artin Commons  \nAfter the tour\, drop by the Martin Commons (2nd floor) 
 for a light reception to celebrate this exhibition with the Asian Culture
  Center and Asian Pacific American Faculty and Staff Council.  \nAbout th
 e Exhibition  \nInspired by Indonesia’s spectacular coral reefs\, acclaim
 ed fiber artist Mulyana (b. 1984\, Bandung\, Indonesia) has created an im
 mersive\, handcrafted seascape where art and ecology meet. Explore colorf
 ul coral reefs\, playful fish\, and fantastical sea creatures — all metic
 ulously hand-knit and crocheted — while learning about how human wellness
  is interconnected with the wellbeing of our oceans.  \n \nThis event is 
 part of 2026 Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month.\n \n \nA
 ll Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, and educational\, cu
 ltural\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other mem
 bers of the Indiana University community.\n \n\nHosted by: Asian Culture 
 Center\, Sidney and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art\n\nAdditional Information
  can be found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12379649
DTEND:20260416T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260331T050034Z
DTSTART:20260416T193000Z
GEO:39.168880;-86.519810
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Curator-led Tour and Reception Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems Exhibition
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12379649
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12379649
X-HOSTS:Sidney and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
