BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
CATEGORIES:Social
CATEGORIES:Social Event
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
CATEGORIES:Emotional Wellness
CATEGORIES:Social Wellness
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Mindful Makers\, a weekly event built around being
  creative\, meeting new people and feeling more confident in yourself and
  your wellness. Each week has a theme - come for one or come for all! We'
 re here to have fun and make cool things.\nJanuary 21: Semester Vision Bo
 ards\nPicture your new semester! Create a vision board that will motivate
  you to achieve this semester. Learn some tips on how to set great goals 
 to help you achieve that vision.\n \nJanuary 28: Meditation and Aromather
 apy\nEver been curious about aromatherapy and how it works? Here's your o
 pportunity to learn more! While you're here\, we'll also practice deep br
 eathing techniques\, progressive relaxation and guided visualization\, an
 d other simple techniques that don't require any special skills or equipm
 ent\n \nFebruary 4: Crochet the Stress Away\nWhether you're a crochet exp
 ert or have never picked up a hook in your life\, we have a place for you
 ! Join us\, learn basic crochet stitches\, and talk about ways to have fu
 n on campus and in the community.\n \nFebruary 11: Origami Ornaments and 
 Overcoming\nSometimes life throws us curve balls. In this Mindful Makers\
 , we'll go through the process of folding origami hearts or cranes\, and 
 using those to make beautiful ornaments that reflect challenges we've ove
 rcome. These cranes carry hope on their wings!\n \nFebruary 18: Air Clay 
 Emotions\nWhat does your angry monster look like? What about your joy? Us
 e air clay to sculpt mini-monsters representing both supportive and chall
 enging emotions\, and learn ways of taming your more wild ones. Remember 
 - not all monsters are scary. Sometimes they're pretty great!\n \nFebruar
 y 25: Love Letters to Your Body and Cookie Decorating\nSometimes we need 
 reminders of how great our bodies can be. In this week's MM\, you'll lear
 n simple bookbinding skills to make an accordion book\, and fill those pa
 ges with what we like about ourselves and our bodies. Join our nutritioni
 st\, Katie Shepherd\, for cookie decorating while you're here!\n \nMarch 
 4: Watercolor Your Values\nOne of the most powerful motivators we have is
  our personal values. Paint a values portrait\, and discuss how you can t
 ie your goals into your values to keep yourself moving forward.\n \nMarch
  11: Sleep Vision Boards\nGetting a good night's sleep is critical toward
 s functioning at your best - but truthfully\, most of us don't get nearly
  the quantity or quality of sleep we need. Create a sleep vision board as
  you learn ways to improve your sleep habits and why sleep is so importan
 t!\n \nMarch 25: Create Your Own Journal\nAnd we do mean from scratch! Le
 arn simple Japanese stitchwork bookbinding to make your own book\, decora
 te it to suit your tastes\, and create a journal you can use however you 
 like! (And if you're new to journaling\, we can work on that as well!)\n 
 \nApril 1: Perler Beads and Mindfulness\nBeing mindful doesn't take anyth
 ing special. Sometimes it can be found in the smallest of things - like t
 he little perler beads! Make yourself an ornament while discovering ways 
 mindfulness can be a part of the everyday things you already do!\n \nApri
 l 8: Gaming with Friends\nDo you know that the oldest known game board is
  9000 years old? We've been playing games for a long time! Well\, not us 
 personally. We're just going to play for a couple of hours. Come and join
  us!\n \nApril 15: Resinate\nNo\, that's not a typo. Learn the basics of 
 resin crafting and make your own ornaments or magnets. While here\, share
  your favorite hobbies and why they matter to you - maybe you'll inspire 
 someone else!\n \nApril 22: Affirmation Jars\nAt the end of the semester\
 , sometimes we need reminders of what motivates us\, makes us special\, o
 r just what matters to us. Create your own affirmation jar and fill it up
  with all those good things. When you're feeling low\, pull one out and g
 ive yourself a boost!\n \nApril 29: Keep Growing\nWhether you're looking 
 forward to graduation\, a summer off\, or one filled with activity\, summ
 er is a great time for growth. Share your upcoming opportunities as you d
 ecorate a pot and select a new plant to nurture. Like plants\, we need ca
 re to keep growing\, so share your ideas for how you're going to care for
  yourself!\n\nHosted by: Health Promotion\n\nAdditional Information can b
 e found at: https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11977508
DTEND:20260422T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260331T050034Z
DTSTART:20260422T213000Z
GEO:39.172430;-86.515960
LOCATION:Wellness House
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mindful Makers
UID:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11977508
URL:https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/11977508
X-HOSTS:Health Promotion
END:VEVENT
